<br>
Un resolutions enforced?  Please see the many many articles and direct quotations of Anthony Zinni, who actually administered the containment of Iraq.  Again, for the 20th time, he is an actual ground commander with actual experiential information on the efficacy of sanctions and the containment of Saddam.  I know it is easier for you to simply ignore him, and what he says, because it doesn't fit in your nice, tidy little worldview.  According to the commander in charge, yes the resolutions were being enforced.<br>
<br>
Iraq as a security threat? /shrug, maybe.   A country that can be fully contained with 23k rotating troops(meaning they were not permanently assigned to the theater--again see Zinni for a good explanation, although I know you won't), funded in large part by our regional allies(you know, the arab countries who won't give us dick now?), does not constitute a serious threat in my eyes.  But what are a few facts among friends, eh?  <br>
<br>
Containment costs to US taxpayers were also denominated in hundreds of millions of dollars, not hundreds of billions.  We could have continued to contain saddam for 30+ years for what we've spent on this war.  We've also forgone signifcant other opportunities (say, for real counter terrorism?) by wasting that money now in a big wad, as opposed to spending it piecemeal to maintain a smaller force.<br>
<br>
For the sake of argument, let's stipulate that Iraq was a threat.  In the world I live in, a state undertakes action against a threat, if at the conclusion of that action, the perceived threats against that state are decreased. This is pretty basic Clausewitz-ian &quot;war as a continuation of policy&quot; stuff. Post-Iraqi &quot;freedom&quot; we are in more danger, not less. Iraq then, is failed <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>policy</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p075.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chilea>Chilea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#333333>(6/17/04 11:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p075.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2705.topic&index=143>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> <br>
